# The @loupeteam packages (lux-connect, lux-react) used by the Loom UI are
# published to GitHub Packages, not npmjs. Map that scope to the GitHub registry
# so `npm install` resolves them. The default registry (npmjs) is unchanged.
#
# Authentication is supplied out-of-band and never committed here:
#   - local dev: a `//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=<token>` line in ~/.npmrc
#   - CI:        injected from a repo secret (see .github/workflows/build.yml)
# The packages are public, so any token with the read:packages scope works.
@loupeteam:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com/
